claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A flowchart illustrating the selection, exclusion, and final cohort counts of adults aged 18–64 vaccinated with recombinant versus standard-dose influenza vaccines over the 2018–2021 seasons. The image does not support the claim: it details participant inclusion/exclusion for vaccine cohorts and provides no information on antigenic matching with WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: No information on antigenic match or WHO/FDA strain selection is present; the image only covers study population flow.
